Subject: Re: [T2] Curtain Material

When I purchased my 74 West, the curtains were old, and rotiing, let
alone some white and black checked stuff---

I went over to Walmart, and checked out what they had--and lo and
behold, they had the right color orange material---

I bought the whole bolt of the stuff, and it wasn't expensive---about
$16.00.

Doubling it up was a peice of cake, and I just sewed in the ends for the
rods to slip through----super easy, super cheap looks good---and not
much light comes throught the material---


Later,

Terry

 
